H.K. Draft Law Proposes Jail Term for False Property Info: Scmp

-- B y   S t a n l e y   J a m e s
-- 
2011-09-27T00:21:08Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-09-27/h-k-draft-law-proposes-jail-term-for-false-property-info-scmp.html
Property company employees and
directors may face as many as seven years in prison for
providing false informaton to potential homebuyers, the  South
China Morning Post  reported, citing Lee Wing-tat, a
member of the government steering committee that drafted the
legislation.  Company representatives may face the prison sentence if
they are found to have provided false or misleading information
either in writing or verbally to boost sales or prices,
according to the report.  Senior company management are at present not held
criminally liable for mistakes or wrongdoing in the selling of
homes, Lee told the Hong Kong-based English-language newspaper.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Stanley James at 
 sjames8@bloomberg.net  